=== 土著歷史 ===
傳統上，紐卡素和下亨特地區（Lower Hunter Region）都是{{le|阿瓦巴卡|Awabakal}}（Awabakal）與{{le|沃里米|Worimi}}（Worimi）族人的聚居地<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hvrf.com.au/pages/hrf/hunter_history_highlights.php|title=Hunter History Highlights|publisher=Hunter Valley Research Foundation|accessdate=14 January 2008|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071225012441/http://www.hvrf.com.au/pages/hrf/hunter_history_highlights.php <!-- Bot retrieved archive -->|archivedate = 25 December 2007}}</ref>，他們稱此地區為馬盧比巴（Malubimba）<ref name=womens_weekly>{{cite journal|url=http://nla.gov.au/nla.news-article55185386|title=Place Names|journal=[[The_Australian_Women's_Weekly|The Australian Women's Weekly]]|page=61|publisher=National Library of Australia|date=13 May 1964|accessdate=22 February 2011|archive-date=2011-03-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110327163310/http://www.trove.nla.gov.au/ndp/del/article/55185386|dead-url=no}}</ref>。
[[File:_Nobbys_Head.jpg|thumb]]

=== 歐洲人定居 ===
1797年9月，海軍上尉{{le|約翰·肖特蘭|John Shortland}}（John Shortland）為首個探索這地區的歐洲人。他在追捕數個從[[悉尼灣|悉尼灣]]偷船的罪犯期間，意外發現這地區<ref name="newc">{{cite web|url=http://www.newcastle.nsw.gov.au/discover_newcastle/visit_our_libraries/discovery_and_founding_of_newcastle|title=Discovery and founding of Newcastle|publisher=[[Newcastle_City_Council|Newcastle City Council]]|accessdate=24 September 2008|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080724032922/http://www.newcastle.nsw.gov.au/discover_newcastle/visit_our_libraries/discovery_and_founding_of_newcastle|archivedate=24 July 2008}}</ref>，及後以時任[[新南威爾士總督|新南威爾士總督]]{{le|約翰·亨特|John Hunter (Royal Navy officer)}}（John Hunter）的名字將之命名<ref name="smh">{{cite web|url=http://www.smh.com.au/news/new-south-wales/newcastle/2005/02/17/1108500198331.html|title=Newcastle|work=The Sydney Morning Herald|date=8 February 2004|accessdate=24 September 2008|archive-date=2014-06-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140608064059/http://www.smh.com.au/news/New-South-Wales/Newcastle/2005/02/17/1108500198331.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。他回程後向上級報告，該處有深水港，而且[[煤礦|煤礦]]含量豐富。往後兩年，在該處採掘的煤礦成為新南威爾士州首批出口貨物<ref name="smh"/>。

因為被送往採礦的都是最危險的罪犯，作為他們所犯罪行的嚴厲懲罰，紐卡素亦沾上了煉獄（hellhole）的惡名<ref name="smh"/>。至19世紀初期，[[亨特河|亨特河]]河口已經經常被各種各樣的人們到訪，包括煤礦工人、[[樵夫|樵夫]]和更多逃脫的罪犯。時任新南威爾士總督{{le|菲利普·吉德利·金|Philip Gidley King}}（Philip Gidley King）決定更加積極地開採當地的[[天然資源|天然資源]]，於1901年建立名為金鎮（King's Town）的囚犯營。這囚犯營只營運了數個月便關閉，至1804年重開，參考[[泰恩河畔纽卡斯尔|英國同名城市]]，並正式改名為紐卡素<ref name=womens_weekly/>。

紐卡素一直為囚犯流放地，至1822年，開放給民眾[[耕作|耕作]]為止<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.environment.gov.au/heritage/places/national/north-road/information.html|title=Old Great North Road more information|publisher=[[Government_of_Australia|Australian Government]]|accessdate=24 September 2008|archive-date=2008-08-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080818051627/http://www.environment.gov.au/heritage/places/national/north-road/information.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

=== 後流放時期 ===
從1823年最後一批囚犯被送到別處開始，紐卡素漸漸吸引到典型的拓荒者在此定居。{{le|紐卡素和亨特河輪船公司|Newcastle and Hunter River Steamship Company}}於1891年成立，並有定期航班往返紐卡素/{{le|莫珀斯 (新南威爾斯)|Morpeth, New South Wales|莫珀斯}}和悉尼。紐卡素與其他澳大利亞城市亦有貨船往來<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.maritime.nsw.gov.au/newcastle.html|title=Ships And Shores And Trading Ports|publisher=NSW Maritime|accessdate=11 July 2008|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080720023338/http://www.maritime.nsw.gov.au/newcastle.html <!-- Bot retrieved archive -->|archivedate = 20 July 2008}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://anmm.gov.au/site/page.cfm?u=630&print=1&S=shopProductInfo&T=shopProductInfo&PRODUCTID=227 |title=The Sixty Miler |publisher=[[Australian_National_Maritime_Museum|Australian National Maritime Museum]] |accessdate=11 July 2008|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070907084254/http://www.anmm.gov.au/site/page.cfm?u=630&print=1&S=shopProductInfo&PRODUCTID=227&T=shopProductInfo |archivedate=7 September 2007 }}</ref>。

=== 1920年代至今 ===
[[第二次世界大戰|第二次世界大戰]]期間，紐卡素為澳大利亞的工業重鎮。1942年6月8日清晨，[[日本皇軍|日本皇軍]]的[[伊號第二十一潛艦|伊號第二十一潛艦]]對紐卡素進行砲擊，受創的設施包括船廠、鋼鐵廠和其他民用建築<ref>{{cite web|url=http://home.st.net.au/~dunn/japsubs/japsshell03.htm|title=Newcastle shelled by a Japanese submarine|date=31 October 2000|accessdate=10 November 2010|archive-date=2011-06-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110610054510/http://home.st.net.au/~dunn/japsubs/japsshell03.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>。
